<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mtext>Value ($)</m:mtext></m:math></entry>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mtext>Total Value ($)</m:mtext></m:math></entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">Quarters</entry>
<entry align="center"/>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>0.25</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="center"/>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left">Pennies</entry>
<entry align="center"/>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>0.01</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
<entry align="center"/>
</row>
<row valign="top">
<entry align="left" namest="c1" nameend="c3"/>
<entry align="center"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mn>2.43</m:mn></m:mrow></m:math></entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
<para id="fs-id1456248">Step 2. <emphasis effect="bold">Identify</emphasis> what you are looking for.</para><para id="fs-id1171103061470"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="2em"/><m:mtext>We are looking for the number of quarters and pennies.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1778537">Step 3. <emphasis effect="bold">Name:</emphasis> Represent the number of quarters and pennies using variables.</para><para id="fs-id1171104458514"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="2em"/><m:mtext>We know Maria has twice as many pennies as quarters. The number of pennies is defined in terms of quarters.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1171104415182"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="2em"/><m:mtext>Let</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mtext>represent the number of quarters.</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:math></para>
<para id="fs-id1171104388047"><m:math><m:mrow><m:mspace width="2em"/><m:mtext>Then the number of pennies is</m:mtext><m:mspace width="0.2em"/><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>q</m:mi><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow></m:math></para>
